        "title": 		"Physical Password Book",
        "body": <<<"
			<p>For those who prefer a tangible solution, a physical password book provides a straightforward way to store passwords offline. Users can manually write down their passwords in the book, keeping it securely stored in a locked drawer or safe. While physical password books offer simplicity and accessibility, they also pose a security risk if lost or stolen, as anyone who gains access to the book can view the stored passwords. For this reason, it's essential to keep the physical password book in a secure location and consider using additional security measures such as disguising passwords or encrypting sensitive information. This solution works well for people who are well organised and keep their documentation safe and secure and can be reasonably assured no one untrustworthy can access the book or be able to use the passwords, through simple manual encryption techniques.To remain useful, it must also be updated regularly, so think about how you’ll manage updating your password book when you’re away from it, how you’ll back it up, and keep it secure if you move this boo before using this technique.</p>
		">>>,
