        "title": 		"Password Managers",
        "body": <<<"
			<p>Password managers offer a secure and convenient solution for storing and managing passwords online. These software applications generate strong, unique passwords for each account, store them in an encrypted vault, and automatically fill in login credentials when needed. Password managers often come with additional features such as password auditing, secure sharing, and multi-factor authentication support. By centralising password management and prioritising security, password managers mitigate the risk of password-related vulnerabilities such as weak passwords, reuse, and theft. However, users should choose a reputable password manager with strong security measures and regularly update their master password for added protection.</p>
		">>>,
        "instruction": "",

		"_items": [
			{
				"title": "Tips for using this password storage technique",
				"body": <<<"
					<p><strong>Use User-Friendly Password Managers:</strong> Start with simple, intuitive password managers like <w.hyperlink href="https://1password.com/">1Password</w.hyperlink> or <w.hyperlink href="https://bitwarden.com/">BitWarden</w.hyperlink> (evaluate and use these tools at your discretion, they are suggestions only), which offer easy setup and user-friendly interfaces.</p>

					<p><strong>Follow Setup Guides:</strong> Use the comprehensive setup guides provided by password managers, which often include video tutorials and step-by-step instructions.</p>

					<p><strong>Enable Browser Extensions:</strong> Install browser extensions provided by the password manager, which can automatically save and fill in passwords for you, making it convenient to use.</p>
